  </sharedSelectionEntryGroups>
  <sharedRules>
    <rule id="96ee-79a8-217a-28a7" name="Rune Armour" hidden="false">
      <description>A model wearing rune armour has a 4+ invulnerable saving throw. If the move is mounted on a jetbike it may take either the normal 3+ armour saving throw or a 4+ rune armour invulnerable save.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="0943-8bb7-8cc4-65f6" name="Warp Jump Generators" hidden="false">
      <description>A model with a Warp Jump Generator may moves up to 12&quot; in the movement phase, ignoring all terrain during the move, but may not finish the move in impassable terrain. 
The unit may make a second jump at the start of the assault phase. They cannot use this jump and charge into combat in the same turn. This second jump moves 2D6&quot; in a nominated direction, and if a double is rolled one member of the squad is removed as a casualty.
The unit also advanced and falls back 3D6&quot; after close combat, ignoring terrain as normal.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="88b7-c132-ffed-9f07" name="Surprise Assault" hidden="false">
      <description>When the Exarch and his squad charge, they gain +2 Attacks instead of the normal +1.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="881b-e3fe-4cf9-4cb7" name="Withdraw" hidden="false">
      <description>If the Exarch&apos;s squad is in close combat at the end of the assault phase, they may fall back to take them out of combat if they wish. All normal rules for a fall back move apply, but the enemy squad may only make a 3&quot; move to consolidate. The Exarch&apos;s unit automatically regroups after the fall back move.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="6570-8481-1f30-3414" name="Crushing Blow" hidden="false">
      <description>The Exarch works out all close combat attacks at +1 Strength.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="cdd4-2891-a528-932c" name="Stealth" hidden="false">
      <description>A squad led by this Exarch may infiltrate if allowed by the mission.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="63bf-dd8b-7daf-793f" name="Acrobatic" hidden="false">
      <description>Before the Exarch makes her close combat attacks, she may be repositioned in contact with any model of your choice in the enemy unit.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="ed74-db03-79f2-e033" name="War Shout" hidden="false">
      <description>When the Exarch charges into combat, during the first round of combat the enemy unit must pass a Leadership test or reduce its WS by -1 for the rest of the assault phase.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="5e2c-19ac-6764-63d6" name="Banshee Masks" hidden="false">
      <description>Models wearing a Banshee Mask always strikes first in hand-to-hand combat in the first round of any assault, regardless of Initiative or other factors. This applies even if they are not in base contact with the enemy. The mask has no effect in additional rounds of combat. In the case of other effects that would allow their enemy to also strike first, both units strike simultaneously.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="ee49-4aa5-13d1-3530" name="Burning Fist" hidden="false">
      <description>In close combat the Exarch may re-roll any failed wound rolls and ignores all armour saves.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="a907-15db-1615-4b1b" name="Tank Hunter" hidden="false">
      <description>The Exarch may re-roll any armour penetration rolls he makes for shooting or in close combat against targets with an armour value.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="59d1-dec4-4d80-b9cc" name="Wraithsight" hidden="false">
      <description>At the start of every Eldar turn, roll a D6 for each Wraithguard unit that is not joined by a Farseer or Warlock. On a roll of a 1, the Wraithguard may do nothing that turn.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="61b3-599d-af54-c39c" name="Difficult Terrain" hidden="false">
      <description>Rangers moving through difficult terrain can roll one additional dice when determing their movement distance.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="6755-7b76-b6aa-3214" name="Cameleoline Cloaks" hidden="false">
      <description>Rangers add +1 to any cover saves it is allowed (e.g. a 5+ cover save becomes a 4+ cover save). If not cover, they are granted a 6+ cover save.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="ab65-4fb9-465e-a84e" name="Distract" hidden="false">
      <description>One model in base contact with the Exarch, chosen by the Eldar player, is at -1 Attacks. This can reduce the model to 0 Attacks.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="3186-1d76-fabf-38c4" name="Defend" hidden="false">
      <description>If the Exarch chooses, he may force enemy models to only hit him on a roll of 6 in close combat, but by doing so he must strike last.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="62c2-695f-6a13-1167" name="Skillful Rider" hidden="false">
      <description>The Exarch and his squad do not roll for difficult terrain.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="be4c-fcc1-62c1-694b" name="Evade" hidden="false">
      <description>The Exarch&apos;s armour saving throw becomes an invulnerable saving throw.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="6006-f98b-12ab-f1d5" name="Swooping Hawk Wings" hidden="false">
      <description>A model with Swooping Hawk Wings moves as if equipped wtih a jump pack. Additionally, a squad with Swooping Hawk Wings may always Deep Strike even if the mission does not normally allow.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="43a2-6d53-eb4a-3729" name="Bounding Leap" hidden="false">
      <description>When making an assault move, the Exarch may add +D6&quot; to the distance he charges. The Exarch may only charge if he is within 6&quot; of the enemy in the assault phase, but he does not have to engage the first model in his path if this extra distance would allow him to reach another model.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="79e6-8a77-2a4b-16a4" name="Sustained Assault" hidden="false">
      <description>For each close combat hit the Exarch makes, he may make an extra attack. These extra attacks, if they hit, allow him to make additional extra attacks.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="d468-2107-0e7e-86e1" name="Implacable Advance" hidden="false">
      <description>Wraithlords can shoot up to two weapons if it moves, and all of its weapons if it stays stationary. It can even fire heavy weapons whilst moving.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="7c2f-b369-5f7f-da26" name="Eldar Energy Field" hidden="false">
      <description>Any ranged attacks against the vehicle&apos;s front and side armour with a Strength greated than 8 counts as Strength 8. Additionally, all front and side attacks may only ever roll +1d6 for their armour penetration (for example, negating the Melta and Ordnance rules). Attacks in close combat or in the rear armour ignore this rule.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="33f8-141c-6263-dfc6" name="Weapons Platform" hidden="false">
      <description>The support weapon has two Guardians as crew. One crewman fires the support weapon and the other is free to fire his own weapon. If both crew are killed the platform is useless (the platform itself can&apos;t be hit). Unlike other anti-grav platforms, the support weapon may not fire if it was moved in the movement phase.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="f63e-9b57-1074-ef2a" name="Fast Shot" hidden="false">
      <description>If the Exarch is firing an assault or heavy weapon, add +1 to the number of shots fired. If instead firing a pistol or rapid fire weapon, then they do not count as moving. Fast Shot may not be used by the Exarch in the same turn as Crack Shot.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="f2fd-294c-434c-acdb" name="Crack Shot" hidden="false">
      <description>The enemy may not making cover saves against shots from the Exarch, and the Exarch may re-roll any failed wound rolls when shooting. Crack Shot may not be used in the same turn the Exarch uses Fast Shot.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="b5d1-5696-e960-ab8c" name="Runes of Warding" hidden="false">
      <description>If an enemy psyker attempts to use a psychic power and the psyker or the target is with 6&quot; of the Farseer, the enemy must take the Psychic test on a 3D6 and discard the lowest roll. Psykers who not normally need to make a Psyhich test are unaffected.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="06eb-6b01-a486-9121" name="Runes of Witnessing" hidden="false">
      <description>A Farseer with runes of witnessing rolls 3D6 and discards the highest when taking a Psychic test. Note, you must use the two lowest dice, even in the case of two ones.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="0fa3-a6b7-33c2-32a4" name="Ghosthelm" hidden="false">
      <description>If the model suffers an attack from the Perils of the Warp he may ignore the attack on a D6 roll of 4+. In addition, any Daemon that is fighting the model in close combat halves (rounding up) its WS.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="b0a6-57c6-99c8-7a34" name="Spirit Stones" hidden="false">
      <description>A psyker with a spirit stone can use two powers each turn instead of one, but they must be different powers.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="b544-c18c-b0cb-90a5" name="Armour of Vaul" hidden="false">
      <description>Instead of an armour save, Arienal must pass an unmodified Leadership test in order to save against any hits she suffers. If the test is failed she loses a wound as normal. The Armour of Vaul is an invulnerable save.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="8ab9-b5a4-c3e8-20d3" name="Alean - The Steed of Khaine" hidden="false">
      <description>Naudhu rides upon a Viper that has been built to allow him to fight from its back, much as Khaine rode to war on the legendary steed Alean. He fights in close combat in the same way as a Dreadnought. He may make a 6&quot; assault move in the assault phase, providing he moved no more than 12&quot; in the movement phase, otherwise he may only fight if assaulted.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="3e45-82de-f527-4b3c" name="Battle Fate" hidden="false"/>
    <rule id="14a9-0694-d982-b67d" name="Star Engines" hidden="false">
      <description>This vehicle may move 2D6&quot; in a straight line during the shooting phase, instead of firing weapons. It may not use the Star Engines in the same turn that it embarks or disembarks transported units.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="fd4f-e837-e39f-53b7" name="Vectored Engines" hidden="false">
      <description>The vehicle may re-roll any failed Difficult Terrain test.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="8efe-b233-9d76-0257" name="Cameleoline Coating" hidden="false">
      <description>Ghost-warriors add +1 to any cover saves it is allowed (e.g. a 5+ cover save becomes a 4+ cover save). If not cover, they are granted a 6+ cover save.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="d917-8503-4e1a-b5bd" name="Gunslingers" hidden="false">
      <description>Eldar Pirates are trained to be ambidextrous and proficient in weilding a myriad of weapons. A model with Gunslinger may opt to fire up to two pistols in the same turn at the same target instead of a single weapon.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="6ded-4863-b16b-dcf3" name="Eldar Pirates" hidden="false">
      <description>Eldar pirates are not seen kindly on by their fellow kin, and the feeling is mutual. Units of Eldar Pirates may only be joined by Independent Characters if they are also Eldar Pirates. The same applies vice-versa, a Eldar Pirate Independent Character may not join units of non-Eldar Pirates.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="04ce-51ca-2b98-3231" name="Holo-field" hidden="false">
      <description>When rolling on the Damage table against this vehicle, the enemy must roll two dice and apply the lowest result.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="6251-dac4-0d4e-8e85" name="Pathfinder Cameleoline Cloaks" hidden="false">
      <description>Pathfinders add +2 to any cover saves it is allowed (e.g. a 5+ cover save becomes a 3+ cover save). If not cover, they are granted a 5+ cover save.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="ac4f-85c3-9c61-60a3" name="Difficult and Impassable Terrain" hidden="false">
      <description>Pathfinders may move through difficult terrain without penalty. Pathfinders may also negotiate impassable terrain as if it were difficult terrain, although they may only roll a single D6 for the distance moved and cannot use fleet of foot whilst in impassable terrain.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="7261-9971-a406-a09f" name="World Weary" hidden="false">
      <description>Pathfinders never take Morale checks for suffering casualties from shooting. They do not have to take &quot;All On Your Own&quot; tests and cannot be pinned. They may always attempt to regroup.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="4d5c-a9d4-43bb-51d5" name="Expert Marksmen" hidden="false">
      <description>When Pathinders fire their long rifles, the shot counts as having AP 1 on a to hit roll of 4, 5, or 6.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="aeb2-ea2e-12aa-2a5d" name="Superb Infiltrators" hidden="false">
      <description>Pathfinders may set up using the Infiltrators rule if the mission allows infiltrators to be used. If there is no special infiltrators rule, the Pathfinders may make one free move after both sides have deployed but before the first turn starts. They cannot use Fleet of Foot during this special move. You may also always deploy your Pathfinders at the start of the battle, even if they would normally have to be kept in reserve.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="b4a6-acb9-a829-7904" name="Expert Pilots" hidden="false">
      <description>Re-roll failed Difficult Terrain tests during the movement phase.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="96fb-a59f-4d87-f6ae" name="Eldar Titan Holo-fields" hidden="false">
      <description>This field provides the unit a 4+ Invulnerable Save against glancing or penetrating hits. The field does not work against close combat attacks.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="8f0c-1fdc-a4aa-e94e" name="Shimmershield" hidden="false">
      <description>A model with a shimmershield, and all members of his unit, benefit from a 5+ invulnerable save in close combat.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="dafb-2bf8-17b2-e60c" name="Powerblades" hidden="false">
      <description>A model with powerblades has +1 attack in close combat, and counts as having a power weapon.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="c83f-9d94-088d-ed3e" name="Dragon Mount" hidden="false">
      <description>The Exodite Knights Dragon mount, unlike normal cavalry, are ferocious fighters in their own right. They may make two extra melee attacks each combat at Weapon Skill 3, Strength 4 and Initiative 1 that does not count towards the amount of attacks the model may normally make.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="82a3-bb38-34d9-ac8b" name="Eldar Exodites" hidden="false">
      <description>Units of Eldar Exodites may only be joined by Independent Characters if they are also Eldar Exodites. The same applies vice-versa, an Eldar Exodites Independent Character may not join units of non-Eldar Exodites.</description>
    </rule>
  </sharedRules>
